Martina Riccioni was killed in a horror car crash in Perth on Easter Monday . 
  She and her friend Antoinettia Caffero were involved in a head-on collision . 
  The 23-year-old was thrown from the car and was killed at the scene . 
  Her family in Italy cannot afford to bring her body home to be buried . 
  They have started a crowdfunding appeal to raise up to $20,000 to transport her body . 
  The transportation of her body could cost as much as $30,000 . 
 